, Dunshaughlin, County Meath, Ireland","Gerrardstown, County Meath, Ireland":"Gerrardstown, County Meath, Ireland","Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland","St Mary's, County Dublin, Ireland":"St Mary's, County Dublin, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Cusack","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Aileen, Brigid, Eamon, Fergus, Seamus.","Irish (of Norman origin): habitational name from Cussac in Guienne, France, named with the Gallo-Roman personal name <i>Cūcius</i> or <i>Cussius</i> + the locative suffix <i>-acum</i>. The surname died out in England, but is common in Ireland, where it was imported at the time of the Anglo-Norman invasion in the 12th century. It has been Gaelicized as <b>de Cíosóg</b>."],"variants":[{"name":"Cuzick","meanings":["Irish and English (Worcestershire): variant of   Cusack  . This form of the surname is no longer found in Ireland and is rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Cusick","meanings":["Irish and Scottish: variant of   Cusack  , now found predominantly in Scotland.","Americanized form of Polish   Kusik   or Czech <b>Kusík</b>, Slovak <b>Kúšik</b> and <b>Kušík</b>.","Americanized form of Croatian <b>Kusić</b>, Croatian and Serbian <b>Kušić</b> (see   Kusic  ), or Serbian <b>Ćušić</b> (see   Cusic  )."]}]},{"name":"Adam","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical.  See  <b>Adam</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Adam Cusack was born about 1189, in St Mary's, County Dublin, Ireland, his father, Geoffrey Mo'r Cusack, was 34 and his mother, Matilda Marie Petite, was 33. He married Lucy de Ledwych in 1219, in Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died in 1248, in Mayo, Ballinrobe, County Mayo, Ireland, at the age of 60."},"et":{"abt 1189–1248":"umbes 1189–1248","1189–1248":"1189